<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Game Tutorial</title>
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
        body {
            background-color: #001f3f; /* Dark blue background */
            color: white; /* Default text color for contrast */
        }
        .accordion-button {
            background-color: #00509e; /* Blue background for accordion buttons */
            color: white; /* White text for accordion buttons */
        }
        .accordion-button:not(.collapsed) {
            background-color: #40E0D0; /* Turquoise when expanded */
            color: black; /* Black text when expanded */
        }
        .accordion-body {
            background-color: #b3b5b5; /* Light gray for accordion body */
            color: black; /* Black text for readability */
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1 class="mb-4"> Welcome to the PowerPlay Tutorial!</h1>

        <div class="accordion" id="tutorialAccordion">
            <!-- about -->
            <div class="accordion-item">
                <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingAbout">
                    <button class="accordion-button" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseAbout" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapseAbout">
                        About the Game üèÄ
                    </button>
                </h2>
                <div id="collapseAbout" class="accordion-collapse collapse show" aria-labelledby="headingAbout" data-bs-parent="#tutorialAccordion">
                    <div class="accordion-body">
                        This is a sports trading card game centered around NBA/WNBA players. Build a team of five and face off against players in order to climb the leaderboard and buy better cards. Cards are based on real NBA/WNBA athletes and their actual performance.
                        <br>
                        <img src="/resources/img/nbawnba.jpg" alt="NBA and WNBA logo" class="img-fluid mt-3">
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- stats -->
            <div class="accordion-item">
                <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingStats">
                    <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseStats" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseStats">
                        Player Stats Breakdown üìä
                    </button>
                </h2>
                <div id="collapseStats" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingStats" data-bs-parent="#tutorialAccordion">
                    <div class="accordion-body">
                        Every card has stats influenced by real-life data:
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Attack:</strong> Derived from points and assists per game.</li>
                            <li><strong>Defense:</strong> Reflective of rebounds per game.</li>
                            <li><strong>Health:</strong> Based on height and weight of the player.</li>
                            <li><strong>Overall:</strong> A calculated average of all key stats above.</li>
                        </ul>
                        For example, these are Joel Embiid's 2023-2024 NBA <strong>stats</strong>:
                        <br>
                        <img src="/resources/img/embiidstats.jpg" alt="Embiid Real Stats" style="width: 400px; height: auto;" class="img-fluid mt-3">
                        <br>
                        <br>
                        And here is the <strong>card</strong> that has been generated for Embiid based off of <strong>calculations</strong> made with those aforementioned <strong>stats</strong>:
                        <br>
                        <img src="/resources/img/embiidcard.jpg" alt="Embiid In-Game Card"  class="img-fluid mt-3">
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- collection -->
            <div class="accordion-item">
                <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingCollection">
                    <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseCollection" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseCollection">Card Collection üìÅ </button>
                </h2>
                <div id="collapseCollection" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingCollection" data-bs-parent="#tutorialAccordion">
                    <div class="accordion-body">
                    Your card collection is the heart of your game experience. There is no limit to your collection, so collecting every card is possible!
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Organizing:</strong> View and manage your collection from your dashboard. If you see room for improvement, try trading one of your cards!</li>
                        <li><strong>Duplicates:</strong> Got duplicates? Use them for trades or save them for strategy-based deck building.</li>
                        <li><strong>Deck Building:</strong> Build your best 5-card lineup using your favorite cards.</li>
                    </ul>
                    Here's an example of a <strong>collection</strong>:
                    <br>
                    <img src="/resources/img/gifs/Collection.gif" alt="Card Collection" class="img-fluid">
                    <br>
                    <br>
                    And here is an example of <strong>deck building</strong>:
                    <br>
                    <img src="/resources/img/gifs/DeckBuilder.gif" alt="Deck Builder" class="img-fluid">
                </div>
                </div>

            <!-- gameplay -->
            <div class="accordion-item">
                <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingGameplay">
                    <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseGameplay" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseGameplay">
                        How Battles Work ‚öîÔ∏è
                    </button>
                </h2>
                <div id="collapseGameplay" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingGameplay" data-bs-parent="#tutorialAccordion">
                    <div class="accordion-body">
                        Players use decks of 5 cards. Each round, one card is picked to battle. Players can randomly roll to increase their attack. Battles then play out, with attack damaging from the opposition's health and defense partially nullifying damage done to oneself. When a card's health reaches 0, the round is over and the other card wins that round. Win more rounds than your opponent to claim victory and earn trophies.
                        <br>
                        Here is an example of a <strong>battle</strong>:
                        <br>
                        <img src="/resources/img/gifs/Battle.gif" alt="Battles" class="img-fluid">
                        <br>

                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- trading -->
            <div class="accordion-item">
                <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingTrading">
                    <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseTrading" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseTrading">
                        Card Trading üîÑ
                    </button>
                </h2>
                <div id="collapseTrading" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingTrading" data-bs-parent="#tutorialAccordion">
                    <div class="accordion-body">
                        Trade with other players to get the cards you need. When trading:
                        <ul>
                            <li>You offer one of your cards and request another.</li>
                            <li>The receiving player can accept or reject the trade.</li>
                            <li>You can cancel a trade you initiated if it's still pending.</li>
                        </ul>
                        Smart trades can help create an unstoppable team, so always be on the lookout!
                        Here is an example of creating a <strong>trade offer</strong>:
                        <br>
                        <img src="/resources/img/gifs/tradeOne.gif" alt="Outgoing Trade" class="img-fluid">
                        <br>
                        <br>
                        And here is an example of <strong>accepting</strong> that same trade:
                        <br>
                        <img src="/resources/img/gifs/tradeTwo.gif" alt="Incoming Trade" class="img-fluid">

                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- money & packs -->
            <div class="accordion-item">
                <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingEconomy">
                    <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseEconomy" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseEconomy">
                        Money, Packs & Progressüí∞
                    </button>
                </h2>
                <div id="collapseEconomy" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingEconomy" data-bs-parent="#tutorialAccordion">
                    <div class="accordion-body">
                        Win battles to earn money and trophies.
                        <ul>
                            <li>PS: You can still earn money if you lose battles, just at a slower rate</li>
                            <li>Use money (100 currency per pack) to buy 5-card packs containing random players.</li>
                            <li>Trophies reflect your skill and progression in the leaderboard (more trophies, higher up on leaderboard).</li>
                        </ul>
                        Here is an example of <strong>opening a pack</strong>:
                        <br>
                        <img src="/resources/img/gifs/OpenPack.gif" alt="Open Pack" class="img-fluid">
                        <br>
                        <br>
                        And here is an example of the <strong>leaderboard</strong>:
                        <br>
                        <img src="/resources/img/gifs/Leaderboard.gif" alt="Leaderboard" class="img-fluid">

                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- get started -->
            <div class="accordion-item">
                <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingStart">
                    <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseStart" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseStart">
                        Ready to Play? üöÄ
                    </button>
                </h2>
                <div id="collapseStart" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingStart" data-bs-parent="#tutorialAccordion">
                    <div class="accordion-body">
                        Register, collect your first set of cards, and dive into competitive battles. Build your ultimate basketball dream team and become the <strong>top card master</strong>!
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
